---
---

<section id="faqs" class="section section-tinted" aria-labelledby="faqs-heading">
  <div class="container-sm">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">FAQs</div>
      <h2 id="faqs-heading" class="section-h2">Common questions before we build.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-wrap reveal">

      <div class="faq-filter-wrap" role="group" aria-label="Filter questions by topic">
        <button class="faq-filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
        <button class="faq-filter-btn" data-filter="general">Getting Started</button>
        <button class="faq-filter-btn" data-filter="website">Website &amp; SEO</button>
        <button class="faq-filter-btn" data-filter="security">Microsoft 365 &amp; Security</button>
        <button class="faq-filter-btn" data-filter="care">Monthly Care</button>
        <button class="faq-filter-btn" data-filter="automation">AI &amp; Automation</button>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list" id="faq-list">

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="general">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do you only work with local businesses?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>ReadyStack Digital focuses on small businesses across Australia, including service providers, consultants, trades, recruitment businesses, clinics, restaurants and other businesses that need a professional online presence and secure digital foundations.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="general">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do I need WordPress?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Not always. Most small businesses only need a fast, professional website with contact forms, SEO setup, secure hosting, domain connection and monthly care. We only recommend WordPress if your business specifically needs full website editing or plugin-heavy features.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="security">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What is Essential Eight and do I need it?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>The Essential Eight is a set of cyber security mitigation strategies published by the Australian Cyber Security Centre (ACSC). It is not a regulatory requirement for most small businesses, but it is increasingly requested by enterprise clients, government agencies, and insurers as evidence of baseline cyber security maturity. If you are bidding on government work, renewing a cyber insurance policy, or onboarding corporate clients, demonstrating Essential Eight Maturity Level 1 alignment can be a genuine business requirement.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="security">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Can you set up Microsoft 365 from scratch?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Our Microsoft 365 for Small Business service covers everything from creating a new tenant to configuring your custom domain, setting up business email with proper MX, SPF, DKIM and DMARC records, enabling Microsoft Teams, OneDrive and SharePoint basics, and enforcing MFA across all accounts. We can also migrate from an existing email provider if needed.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="security">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What is the difference between Online Presence + M365 and Secure SMB Foundation?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Online Presence + M365 gives you a professional website and a properly configured Microsoft 365 tenant with business email, MFA, Teams and OneDrive. Secure SMB Foundation builds on that by adding Essential Eight Maturity Level 1 controls — Intune device baseline, conditional access policies, application control basics, restricted admin privileges, and a hardened M365 tenant. Choose Secure SMB Foundation if you need to demonstrate formal cyber security maturity for clients, insurers, or government tenders.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="security">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do I need Essential Eight if I am a small business?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Not always — but increasingly yes. The trigger is usually external: a corporate client's supplier requirements, a government tender panel that asks for evidence of cyber security posture, or a cyber insurance renewal where the insurer wants to see baseline controls. If none of those apply to your business right now, the Online Presence Starter or Online Presence + M365 packages are likely sufficient, with the option to uplift later.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="website">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Is SEO included?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. Every website includes basic SEO setup, including page titles, meta descriptions, sitemap, heading structure, image alt text, schema markup and Google Search Console setup.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="care">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Can you manage my domain and hosting?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. We can help register or connect your domain, configure DNS, connect hosting, manage SSL and keep the technical setup monitored through monthly care.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="care">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Is business email included?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Business email is included in the Online Presence + M365 and Secure SMB Foundation packages. It is also available as a standalone service through our Microsoft 365 for Small Business or Email Security &amp; Domain Protection offerings. All email setups include proper MX, SPF, DKIM and DMARC records.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="website">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Will my website be secure?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Yes. We include secure website foundations such as HTTPS, SSL checks, secure hosting setup, DNS checks and form testing. Where suitable, we use lightweight static websites to reduce unnecessary plugin and admin-login risks.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="care">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What does monthly care include?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Monthly care is available at three tiers. Website Care ($100/month) covers hosting, domain and DNS checks, SSL monitoring, form testing and basic SEO monitoring. Website + M365 Care ($300/month) adds M365 user lifecycle management, MFA review, DMARC reports and a monthly security review. Full Stack Care ($600/month) adds Essential Eight monitoring, a monthly security report and priority support.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="automation">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What is an AI agent and how can it help my small business?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>An AI agent is a piece of software that can handle tasks or conversations on your behalf, automatically. For small businesses, practical examples include: an AI chat agent on your website that answers customer questions about your services, pricing and bookings at any hour; automated lead follow-up that sends a reply the moment a contact form is submitted; and workflow automations that handle repetitive tasks like appointment reminders, invoice nudges and review requests. The goal is not to replace your team — it is to remove the manual work that happens outside business hours or falls through the cracks.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="automation">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do I need Microsoft 365 to use AI automation?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>Not for all automations. AI chat agents and lead automation workflows can be set up independently of Microsoft 365. However, Microsoft 365 Copilot — which brings AI into Teams, Outlook, Word and Excel — does require an eligible Microsoft 365 Business plan. If you are already on M365 or planning to set it up, adding Copilot is a natural next step. We can advise on the right combination based on your current tools and budget.</p></div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item" data-cat="website">
          <button type="button" class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do you offer unlimited edits?</span>
            <svg class="faq-arrow" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 7l4 4 4-4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.7" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-a"><p>No. Monthly care includes small updates only. Larger design changes, new pages, copywriting, SEO campaigns or custom features are quoted separately.</p></div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
